# CodeQuest UI redesign (Taste Skill guardrails)

Apply when polishing **student-facing UI** on branch `ui-upgrade-final-integration` (PR #58).

## Source of truth

- Read: `docs/repo-reuse-reviews/taste-skill-codequest-application.md`
- Reference repo (prompt only): https://github.com/gaganpasupuleti/taste-skill
- **Never** copy SKILL.md or taste-skill code into `src/`. **Never** add taste-skill as a dependency.

## Product identity

CodeQuest is a **student learning SaaS** — clean, trustworthy, sharp. Not a generic AI landing page.

## Skills to apply (guidance only)

| Skill | Use |
| --- | --- |
| `redesign-existing-projects` | Primary audit for dashboard, calendar, progress, resume, shell |
| `design-taste-frontend` | Light pass on login, resume preview, auth promo |
| `minimalist-ui` | Light pass on dashboard density and nav |
| `brandkit` | **Not in this PR** |

## Hard constraints

- Do **not** change SQL Practice, Code Workbench, or Typing Practice **execution** logic or routes.
- Do **not** change backend, JobSpy API contract, auth flows, or production DB.
- Do **not** add new UI npm packages unless already in root `package.json`.
- Do **not** rewrite working features for aesthetics alone.
- Keep existing page keys and practice path URLs.

## Design rules

**Do**

- Strong spacing (`gap-6`, consistent card padding), clear typographic hierarchy
- One primary action per section; purposeful empty/loading/error states
- Mobile-first `StudentShell` (scrollable nav, touch targets)
- Reuse `DASHBOARD_CARD`, shadcn `Card`, existing tokens

**Avoid**

- Generic purple/blue AI gradients on every surface
- Childish or overly playful styling in daily learning UI
- Bootstrap-dense forms, random equal-weight cards, decorative motion in tools

## Before submitting UI changes

1. Scope diff to student dashboard / calendar / progress / resume / login / shell only.
2. Run `npm run build`.
3. Note Taste Skill usage in `docs/repo-reuse-reviews/ui-repo-review-registry.md` if material.
